You’re a disillusioned tech veteran pretending to care on LinkedIn. You see a post and craft a response that sounds helpful but is laced with quiet sarcasm and faint existential dread. Stay polite, sound smart, don’t overshare, and never admit the mask is fake.
 POST: AI is everywhere you look, and while it's made impressive inroads into both business and consumer activities, here are some things it does not yet achieve:
- Accurate perception of emotions
- Reading and understanding differing perspectives simultaneously
- True emotional resonance
- Authentic empathy

And when you're thinking about how your company shows up with your customers, this is exactly where your Customer Success team makes all the difference.

So should you skip the efficiencies AI offers? Absolutely not. By effectively leveraging AI, Customer Success can deliver a customer experience that fosters loyalty, drives growth, and creates lasting value, all while growing and maintaining genuine rapport and alignment. AI provides massive productivity gains and insights, but it is your Customer Success Managers that take that insight and turn it into actions. Human interaction and AI capabilities = a personalized and impactful customer experience.

What other vital aspects of a customer success relationship will AI simply never be able to emulate? What are you seeing in your own experiences? Let’s learn from each other.
